   at the path: /home/student/exam-shortcut.  (3 pts)


TASK 2 — User, Group, and Password Policy  (20 pts, ~15 min)
--------------------------------------------------------------
You are provisioning accounts for a new team of database administrators.

NOTE: The dbteam group already exists on your system — do not delete and
recreate it, just confirm the GID matches and proceed.

1. Create a group named dbteam with GID {{ exam_gid }}.  (3 pts)

2. Create a user named {{ exam_username }} with:
   - dbteam as a supplementary group  (2 pts)
   - Initial password: Welcome1  (2 pts)
   - Password must be changed on first login  (3 pts)

3. Set the following password policy for {{ exam_username }}:  (6 pts — 2 each)
   - Minimum days between password changes: 7
   - Maximum days before password change is required: 60
   - Account expiry date: {{ exam_expiry }}

4. Allow {{ exam_username }} to run any command with sudo without a password
   prompt. Use a dedicated file in /etc/sudoers.d/.  (4 pts)


TASK 3 — File Permissions and Collaborative Directory  (20 pts, ~15 min)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
The dbteam group needs a shared workspace where all members can create and
modify files, but cannot delete each other's work.

1. Create the directory /home/{{ exam_workspace }}.  (2 pts)
2. Set the group owner to dbteam.  (3 pts)
3. Set permissions so that:
   - Owner has full read, write, and execute access  (1 pt)
   - Group members have read, write, and execute access  (2 pts)
   - All other users have no access  (2 pts)
4. Set the SGID bit on the directory.  (4 pts)
5. Set the sticky bit on the directory.  (4 pts)
6. Configure {{ exam_username }}'s shell so that umask is persistently
   set to 007.  (2 pts)

Expected final permissions: drwxrws--T


