TASK 6 — Mount a File System and Search for Files  (15 pts, ~15 min)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
A new disk has been attached to your system as /dev/sdb with one
partition /dev/sdb1 (already formatted as XFS).

1. Create a mount point at {{ exam_mount }}.  (2 pts)

2. Mount /dev/sdb1 persistently via /etc/fstab. Use either the UUID
   (recommended, find it with: lsblk -fp) or /dev/sdb1.
   The mount must survive a reboot.  (5 pts)

3. After mounting, create a file at {{ exam_mount }}/mounted.txt
   containing exactly:
   {{ exam_mount_text }}
   (2 pts)

4. Find all files in /etc larger than 50 KB and save the full path
   list to {{ exam_mount }}/large-files.txt.  (3 pts)

5. Find all files in /var owned by user root and group root with
   permissions exactly 640, and save the full path list to
   {{ exam_mount }}/perms-files.txt.  (3 pts)

Tip: Use lsblk -fp to find the UUID. Suppress find errors with 2>/dev/null.

